f={{sfnref|Ross|Lewis|1958b}} |title=The Strato-Lab Balloon System for High Altitude Research |last1=Ross |first1=Malcolm |last2=Lewis |first2=M. Lee |journal=The Journal of Aviation Medicine |volume=29 |number=5 |pages=375\u2013385 |date=June 1958}}\n* <!--{{Sfn|Ross|1959}}-->{{cite journal |last=Ross |first=Malcolm |date=May 1959 |title=Reactions of a Balloon Crew in a Controlled Environment |journal=The Journal of Aviation Medicine |publisher=Aerospace Medical Association |url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/9912687_Reactions_of_a_balloon_crew_in_a_controlled_environment  |volume=30 |number=3 |pages=326\u2013333 |id= |url-access=registration |access-date=2015-03-27 |pmid=13654207}}\n* <!--{{Sfn|Ross|Edwards|1961}}-->{{cite journal |last1=Ross |first1=Malcolm |last2=Edwards |first2=Walter |date=November 1961 |title=Project Strato-Lab High 5: We Saw the World from the Edge of Space |url=http://ngm-beta.nationalgeographic.com/archive/we-saw-the-world-from-the-edge-of-space/ |journal=National Geographic Magazine |location=Washington, D.C. |publisher=The National Geographic Society |pages=671\u2013685 |volume=120 |number=5 |url-access=registration |access-date=2015-03-26}}\n* <!--{{Sfn|Ross|1962}}-->{{cite conference |last=Ross |first=Malcolm |date=May 8\u201310, 1962 |title=A Consideration of the U.S. Navy Strato-Lab Balloon Program and Its Contributions to Manned Space Flight |conference=Second National Conference on the Peaceful Uses of Space, Seattle, WA |journal=Proceedings of the Second National Conference on the Peaceful Uses of Space |location=Washington, D.C. |publisher=NASA |id=SP-8 |page=261}}\n* <!--{{Sfn|Ryan|1995}}-->{{cite book |ref={{sfnref|Ryan|1995}} | last = Ryan | first = Craig | year = 1995 | title = The Pre-Astronauts: Manned Ballooning on the Threshold of Space | publisher = US Naval Institute Press | location = Annapolis | isbn = 1-55750-732-5 | url = https://archive.org/details/preastronautsman00ryan}}\n* <!--{{Sfn|Shayler|2000}}-->{{cite book | last = Shayler | first = David J. | year = 2000 | title = Disasters and Accidents in Manned Space Flight | publisher = Springer | location = Berlin | isbn = 1-85233-225-5}}\n* <!--{{Sfn|Wilson|Winfrey|McDole|2012}}-->{{cite book |ref={{sfnref|Wilson|Winfrey|McDole|2012}} | last1 = Wilson | first1 = Jodie Steelman | last2 = Winfrey | first2 = Emily Griffin | last3 = McDole | first3 = Rebecca | year = 2012 | title = Hidden History of Montgomery County, Indiana | chapter = The Highest Achiever of Linden High School | pages = 8\u201316 | publisher = The History Press | location = Stroud, Gloucestershire, UK | isbn = 978-1609495220}}\n\n==Malcolm Ross Papers==\n*[http://siris-archives.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?uri=full=3100001~!228965!0 ''Malcolm D. Ross Papers''] including photographs, notes, correspondence, and medical records, are archived at the Smithsonian Institution, NASM Archives Accession No. 1998-0048. National Air and Space Museum. Archives Division MRC 322, Washington, D.C., 20560\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080414105223/http://web.mac.com/bemidji2/iWeb/Site/About%20Man%20High/F5C72A92-F4FA-4C00-BCED-9F4D8A5B5F69.html Balloon Ancestors of Space Flight] (from ''Touching Space: The Story of Project Manhigh'')\n*[http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,00.html ''The Fourteen Mile Drop''] Monday, November 19, 1956; [http://www.time.com ''TIME.com''] article about the rapid descent that ended the 8 November 1956 record breaking flight.\n*[http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=8975 John F. Kennedy: Remarks on Presenting the Harmon Trophies] Thursday, October 18, 1962 (The American Presidency Project)\n*[http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,00.html ''Shivering Look at Venus''] Monday, December 14, 1959; [http://www.time.com ''TIME.com''] article about the 28 November 1959 flight to observe Venus\n*[http://stratocat.com.ar/artics/stratolab-e.htm Stratolab, an Evolutionary Stratospheric Balloon Project