were-men-and-most-had-these-underlying-illnesses|newspaper=[[The Journal News]]|via=[[Times Herald-Record]]|date=April 8, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\nLater data showed that African American and Latino patients in the state outside of the city accounted for a greater share of the deaths from the disease than their share of the overall population. Data from the city had not been available at the time.<ref>{{cite news|last=Robinson|first=David|title=Coronavirus in NY: COVID-19 race, ethnicity data show black, Hispanic population at higher risk|url=https://www.recordonline.com/news/20200408/coronavirus-in-ny-covid-19-race-ethnicity-data-show-black-hispanic-population-at-higher-risk|newspaper=[[Gannett]] New York|via=''[[Times Herald-Record]]''|date=April 8, 2020|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Graphs===\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=700\n|height=400\n|colors=#FF4343\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|yAxisTitle=No. of cases (cumulative)\n|legend=Legend\n| yAxisMin = 1\n| yAxisMax =\n<!--Please clipboard copy the \"}x=...\" and \"y1=...\" lines from the log plot of total cases when you update these charts-->\n\n<!--Search string CASES_X-->\n|x= Feb 26, Feb 27, Feb 28, Feb 29, Mar 1, Mar 2, Mar 3, Mar 4, Mar 5, Mar 6, Mar 7, Mar 8, Mar 9, Mar 10, Mar 11, Mar 12, Mar 13, Mar 14, Mar 15, Mar 16, Mar 17, Mar 18, Mar 19, Mar 20, Mar 21, Mar 22, Mar 23, Mar 24, Mar 25, Mar 26, Mar 27, Mar 28, Mar 29, Mar 30, Mar 31, Apr 1, Apr 2, Apr 3, Apr 4, Apr 5, Apr 6, Apr 7, Apr 8, Apr 9, Apr 10, Apr 11, Apr 12, Apr 13, Apr 14, Apr 15, Apr 16, Apr 17, Apr 18, Apr 19, Apr 20, Apr 21, Apr 22, Apr 23\n\n<!--Search string CASES_Y-->\n|y1=0,0,0,0,0,1,2,11,23,31,76,106,142,150,220,327,421,613,615,967,1578,3038,5704,8403,11727,15800,20884,25681,30841,37877,44876,52410,59648,66663,75833,83948,92506,102987,113833,123160,131815,139875,151061,161779,172348,181026,189033,195749,203020,214454,223691,230597,241712,247815,253195,2